text: Mischa Bredewold (born 20 June 2000) is a Dutch professional racing cyclist from Hoogland, who currently rides since 2021 for UCI Women's Continental Team Parkhotel Valkenburg Cycling Team. Bredewold won the first stage of the 2021 Baloise Ladies Tour and the overall young rider classification. At the 2022 European Road Championships she won the bronze medal in the under-23 team time trial event. She competed at the 2022 Tour de France Femmes. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch cyclists Category:Sportswomen
